  "__requires": [],
  "annotations": {
    "list": [
      {
        "builtIn": 1,
        "datasource": {
          "type": "datasource",
          "uid": "grafana"
        },
        "enable": true,
        "hide": true,
        "iconColor": "rgba(0, 211, 255, 1)",
        "name": "Annotations & Alerts",
        "type": "dashboard"
      }
    ]
  },
  "description": "Lab power \u2014 one honest number per measurement tier. ACCOUNTING MODEL: every TOTAL/KPI sums series from EXACTLY ONE tier; cross-tier numbers only appear side-by-side or as a labeled ratio, never summed. TIERS: WALL = whole-UPS %load \u00d7 nameplate (ESTIMATE; apc1500/cyberpower1500) \u2014 most-upstream authority. BRANCH = real downstream measurement (AP7900 bank amps\u2192W; CRS328 PoE-out W). HOST-ACTUAL = BMC chassis watts (TrueNAS IPMI). COMPONENT = none usable (RAPL/DCGM/PD/NVDIMM all absent or read 0). DOUBLE-COUNT GUARDS: (1) never sum WALL + BRANCH PDU \u2014 the AP7900 hangs off a UPS and is already inside its WALL. (2) brick-board PoE-out (4\u20135 W) is incidental, NOT their real draw. (3) the PDU bank has one amp reading \u2014 no per-outlet split. (4) ether24 is a trunk, excluded. (5) TrueNAS is an off-PDU island, kept separate (UPS linkage unverified). GAPS surfaced: per-device x86/ARM watts (ms01/hpg5/p330/cm3588/4 brick boards), per-board Radxa split, casval GPU power, vscode devhost, switch self-consumption \u2014 no source exists. UNITS: all normalized to watts; energy = gauge integral (kWh), no joule counters. All source metrics live in user-workload-monitoring, fanned-in via thanos-querier. No counter rates \u2014 every source is an instantaneous gauge.",
  "editable": true,
  "fiscalYearStartMonth": 0,
  "graphTooltip": 1,
  "links": [],
  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "stat",
      "title": "WALL \u2014 Total UPS power",
      "description": "WALL tier (ESTIMATE). Sum of %load \u00d7 nameplate W across selected UPSes \u2014 the most-upstream honest fleet number. Single tier; nothing downstream (PDU/PoE/IPMI) is added on top.",
      "datasource": {
        "type": "prometheus",
        "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 4,
        "w": 6,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "color": {
            "mode": "thresholds"
          },
          "decimals": 0,
          "mappings": [],
          "thresholds": {
            "mode": "absolute",
            "steps": [
              {
                "color": "green",
                "value": null
              }
            ]
          },
          "unit": "watt"
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "colorMode": "value",
        "graphMode": "area",
        "justifyMode": "auto",
        "orientation": "auto",
        "reduceOptions": {
          "calcs": [
            "lastNotNull"
          ],
          "fields": "",
          "values": false
        },
        "textMode": "value",
        "wideLayout": true
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "prometheus",
            "uid": "${DS_PROMETHEUS}"
          },
          "editorMode": "code",
          "expr": "sum(network_ups_tools_ups_load{ups=~\"$ups\"} / 100 * on(ups) group_left() network_ups_tools_ups_realpower_nominal)",
          "refId": "A",
          "format": "time_series",
          "instant": true,
          "range": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
